This article highlights the importance of volunteering and calls on Americans to serve their communities. It emphasizes the selfless acts of volunteers who engage in various activities such as rebuilding homes, educating youth, supporting veterans, and combating climate change. The article also mentions the 30th anniversary of AmeriCorps, a federal agency that has mobilized over a million Americans to serve their neighbors and respond to crises. President Biden expresses his commitment to strengthening AmeriCorps and expanding opportunities for Americans to volunteer overseas through the Peace Corps. The article further mentions the United We Stand Summit, which aims to address hate-fueled violence and promote unity through community partnerships and service events. President Biden proclaims April 16 to April 22, 2023, as National Volunteer Week, urging all Americans to participate in service projects and make service a part of their daily lives.